Description of problem:
LUNs that are already attached to the main storage domain, show up as attachable to VMs in the direct LUN dialog

Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable):


How reproducible:
100%

Steps to Reproduce:
1. Create a Storage Domain & attach an FC LUN
2. Create a VM and click "attach disk / external (direct lun)
3. Look for LUN thats already in use for the Storage Domain 

Actual results:
The LUN from the main Storage domain is listed as available

Expected results:
It should be shown greyed out or unavailable

Additional info:
RHEL 6.6 RHEV-M
RHEL 7.1 RHEL-H
*** This bug has been marked as a duplicate of bug 906252 ***
